1997	% $\varphi : \spec \K \to \grass(r,d)$, and moreover all $d\times d$ minors
1998	% $X^J_K$ satisfy $\nu(g(P^J_K)) \ge 0$. As the minor $X^J_J$ is identity, it
1999	% follows from the above that in fact $\nu(g(x^J_{p,q}))\ge 0$ for all entries of
2000	% $X^J$. Therefore, the map $g : \Z[X^J] \to \K$ factors uniquely via
2001	% $\Rr \subset \K$. The resulting morphism of schemes
2002	% $\spec \Rr \to U^J \hra \grass(r,d)$ prolongs
