2067	\section{Out of scope}
2068	\label{sec:gr_out_of_scope}
2069	
2070	This chapter constructs the Grassmannian \emph{scheme} \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\) over
2071	the absolute base \(\mathbb{Z}\) and establishes its smoothness, separatedness
2072	and properness. The following constructions are deferred to later chapters and
2073	are not treated here:
2074	\begin{itemize}
2075	  \item \textbf{The tautological/universal quotient} \(u : \mathcal{O}^{\oplus
2076	    r}_{\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)} \twoheadrightarrow \mathcal{U}\) and the determinant
2077	    line bundle \(\det \mathcal{U}\) with its Pl\"ucker embedding.
2078	  \item \textbf{The functor-of-points representability} of \(\mathrm{Gr}(r,d)\)
2079	    -- that it represents \(\mathrm{Grass}(r,d) =
2080	    \Quot^{d,\mathcal{O}_{\mathbb{Z}}}_{\oplus^r \mathcal{O}_{\mathbb{Z}} /
2081	    \mathbb{Z} / \mathbb{Z}}\); this is blueprinted as
2082	    \cref{thm:grassmannian_representable} in
2083	    \cref{chap:Picard_QuotScheme}.
2084	  \item \textbf{The relative version over a general base \(S\)} with a locally
2085	    free sheaf \(V\) of rank \(r\): the scheme \(\mathrm{Gr}_S(V,d)\) obtained by
2086	    base change and gluing over a trivialising cover of \(V\). The
2087	    absolute-over-\(\mathbb{Z}\) construction of this chapter is the input to
2088	    that base change.
2089	\end{itemize}
